the golijska moravica or simply moravica (serbian cyrillic: голијска моравица or моравица) is a river in western serbia. with a length of 98 km, it is the longer headstream of the zapadna morava (it forms it with the đetinja), and thus, of the velika morava. its name, moravica, means little morava in serbian, and it also gives its name to the surrounding region and the modern moravica district of serbia.